verbose_text: RAGE is known to increase the activity of RANKL leading to osteoclastogenesis in bone [XREF_BIBR] and has been associated with atherosclerotic lesions and vascular calcification by increasing the expression of bone morphogenetic protein 4 in arteries [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR] and is thought to cause a phenotypic switch of VSMCs to an osteoblast like phenotype [XREF_BIBR].
